<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="179" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,854,1349]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,926,953]" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Medium to large coenagrionids (
<quantity box="[687,810,927,953]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.45" metricValueMax="6.1" metricValueMin="2.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="179" unit="mm" value="44.5" valueMax="61.0" valueMin="28.0">28–61 mm</quantity>
, 
<figureCitation box="[820,890,927,953]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1433,1458]" captionTargetBox="[160,1429,532,1406]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,525,1408]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male habitus: (a) caldense, São Roque de Minas, at ECOEVO; (b) caldense, Poços de Caldas, at FAAL; (c) canaanense, Santa Tereza, at FAAL; (d) mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (e) ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes PARATYPE, at FAAL; (f) waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875353" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875353/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
a–f, 5a–j); male anal appendages forcipate with a medial longitudinal ridge on medial surface of cercus: apically armed with a rounded sclerotized lobe (dorsal plate); the ventral portion of which forms a ventrobasal expansion varying in size (see 
<figureCitation box="[1042,1117,999,1025]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="7.[151,250,975,1000]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,184,944]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,181,949]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male anal appendages; (a–d) ♂ caldense, Poços de Caldas, at FAAL; (e–h) ♂ caldense, São Roque de Minas, at LESTES; (i–l) ♂ canaanense, Santa Tereza, at FAAL; (m–p) ♂ mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (q–t) ♂ ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes PARATYPE, at FAAL; (u–x) ♂ waltheri, Jaboticatubas, at FAAL." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875357" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875357/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
a–x, 8a–h); paraprocts vestigial with an acute tip, shorter or subequal to 1/2 cercus; genital ligula with an inner fold next to flexure, sclerotized lateral process at the flexure, apex entire (e.g. 
<figureCitation box="[664,729,1071,1098]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1348,1373]" captionTargetBox="[172,1418,191,1313]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[160,1427,181,1323]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male genital ligula; (a) caldense, Poços de Caldas PARATYPE, at MNRJ probably lost; (b) caldense, SCNP PARA- TYPE of M. franciscoi, at ABMM; (c) canaanense, Santa Tereza, at RWG; (d) mecistogastrum, Cachoeira de Macacu, at RWG; (e) ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes, at RWG; (f) waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875359/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
a–b) or bifid (
<figureCitation box="[883,964,1071,1097]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1348,1373]" captionTargetBox="[172,1418,191,1313]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[160,1427,181,1323]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male genital ligula; (a) caldense, Poços de Caldas PARATYPE, at MNRJ probably lost; (b) caldense, SCNP PARA- TYPE of M. franciscoi, at ABMM; (c) canaanense, Santa Tereza, at RWG; (d) mecistogastrum, Cachoeira de Macacu, at RWG; (e) ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes, at RWG; (f) waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875359/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
), surpassing level of or almost at the same level of inner fold (
<figureCitation box="[373,456,1107,1133]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1348,1373]" captionTargetBox="[172,1418,191,1313]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[160,1427,181,1323]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male genital ligula; (a) caldense, Poços de Caldas PARATYPE, at MNRJ probably lost; (b) caldense, SCNP PARA- TYPE of M. franciscoi, at ABMM; (c) canaanense, Santa Tereza, at RWG; (d) mecistogastrum, Cachoeira de Macacu, at RWG; (e) ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes, at RWG; (f) waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875359" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875359/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 4e</figureCitation>
); female posterior lobe of prothorax slightly convex, uni- (
<figureCitation box="[1125,1192,1107,1134]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,965,990]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,186,935]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,181,940]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Female posterior lobe of prothorax; (a) caldense, Poços de Caldas ALLOTYPE, at MNRJ; (b) caldense, SCNP, at ECOEVO; (c) canaanense, Santa Tereza ALLOTYPE, at MNRJ; (d) mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (e) ribeiroi, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (f) waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875363" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875363/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
a–c) or trilobate (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,965,990]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,186,935]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1436,181,940]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Female posterior lobe of prothorax; (a) caldense, Poços de Caldas ALLOTYPE, at MNRJ; (b) caldense, SCNP, at ECOEVO; (c) canaanense, Santa Tereza ALLOTYPE, at MNRJ; (d) mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (e) ribeiroi, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (f) waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875363" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875363/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
d–f) in dorsal view; in lateral view, posterior margin of prothorax entire (
<figureCitation box="[975,1055,1143,1169]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1157,1182]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,187,1122]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1437,181,1131]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Female prothorax in lateral view; (a) caldense, Poços de Caldas PARATYPE, at ABMM; (b) canaanense, Santa Tereza ALLOTYPE, at MNRJ; (c) mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (d) ribeiroi, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (e) waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875365" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875365/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 7c</figureCitation>
) or divided (
<figureCitation box="[1198,1264,1143,1169]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1157,1182]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,187,1122]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1437,181,1131]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Female prothorax in lateral view; (a) caldense, Poços de Caldas PARATYPE, at ABMM; (b) canaanense, Santa Tereza ALLOTYPE, at MNRJ; (c) mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (d) ribeiroi, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (e) waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875365" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875365/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
a–b, d–e) in the posterior lobe region, notopleural suture a sinuous (
<figureCitation box="[739,820,1179,1205]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1157,1182]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,187,1122]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1437,181,1131]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Female prothorax in lateral view; (a) caldense, Poços de Caldas PARATYPE, at ABMM; (b) canaanense, Santa Tereza ALLOTYPE, at MNRJ; (c) mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (d) ribeiroi, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (e) waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875365" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875365/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 7c</figureCitation>
) or smoothly curved line (
<figureCitation box="[1125,1209,1179,1206]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1157,1182]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,187,1122]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1437,181,1131]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Female prothorax in lateral view; (a) caldense, Poços de Caldas PARATYPE, at ABMM; (b) canaanense, Santa Tereza ALLOTYPE, at MNRJ; (c) mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (d) ribeiroi, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (e) waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875365" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875365/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 7b</figureCitation>
); S8 with no vulvar spine (
<figureCitation box="[225,369,1215,1242]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1500,1525]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,190,1467]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1435,181,1474]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Female structures of Minagrion allotypes probably lost during the fire at MNRJ in 2018; (a–c) caldense, Poços de Caldas; (d–f) canaanense, Santa Tereza; (g–i) ribeiroi (Telagrion ribeiroi), Recreio dos Bandeirantes; (j–l) waltheri (Telagrion serracipoense), Jaboticatubas." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875369/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Fig. 9c, f, i, l</figureCitation>
); vulvar laminae always surpassing posterior margin of S10, reaching or not the level of cercus; presence of a longitudinal process (here called tubercle) on both sexes, which consists in a thin projection on the venter of S1, larger on males (e.g. 
<figureCitation box="[538,615,1287,1314]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1265,1290]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,187,1233]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,181,1239]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. S1 tubercle; (a) ♂ caldense, Poços de Caldas, at FAAL; (b) ♂ caldense, São Roque de Minas, at LESTES; (c) ♀ caldense ALLOTYPE, Poços de Caldas, at MNRJ; (d) ♀ caldense, SCNP, at ECOEVO; (e) ♂ canaanense, Santa Tereza, at FAAL; (f) ♀ canaanense ALLOTYPE, Santa Tereza, at MNRJ; (g) ♂ mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (h) ♀ mecistogastrum, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (i) ♂ ribeiroi, Recreio dos Bandeirantes PARATYPE, at FAAL; (j) ♀ ribeiroi, Salesópolis, at FAAL; (k) ♂ waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM; (l) ♀ waltheri, São Gonçalo do Rio Preto, at ABMM." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3875355" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3875355/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="179">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
a–l).
</paragraph>
